      "Witness statements collected",
      "Contributing factors identified"
    ],
    "summary": "During casing installation operations on the Noble Bully I drilling rig, an injured person (IP) placed his hand into a hinged section of a 1,250 ton Rotary Mounted Slips (RMS) component while attempting to stop its rotation. The hinged side rapidly closed with significant force, crushing the IP's index, middle and ring finger on his left hand. The incident was caused by poor hand placement in a known pinch point, with contributing factors including uneven hoisting causing rotation, lack of hazard markings, absence of safety guarding, and fatigue from excessive work hours.",
    "recommendations": [],
